                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 838.00/821.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>National Assembly obtained unexpected quorum and elected Oreste Zamor President
                    by constitutional majority today. The matter of recognition will be imminent
                    tomorrow and in order to avoid embarrassing international situation I would
                    respectfully suggest that <pb facs="0454" n="338" xml:id="pg_338"/> it is
                    imperative that I have instructions immediately. I am reliably informed that
                    there is no disposition on the part of any foreign representative to act
                    independently and that all await the action of my Government. Zamor’s elevation
                    to the Presidency undoubtedly accomplished by revolutionary means. His entry
                    into the city was peaceable and he has preserved order since coming in.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
